solution: ```class Solution {
    public int leastOpsExpressTarget(int x, int target) {
        return dfs(x, target, 0);
    }
    private int dfs(int x, int target, int k) {
        if (x == target) return 0;
        if (target == 0) return 0;
        if (target == 1) return k == 0 ? 2 : k;
        long p = 1;
        int cnt = 0;
        while (p * x < target) {
            p *= x;
            cnt++;
        }
        if (p == target) return cnt;
        int res = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
        if (p * x - target < target) {
            res = Math.min(res, dfs(x, (int)(p * x - target), k + cnt + 1) + cnt + 1);
        }
        res = Math.min(res, dfs(x, (int)(target - p), k) + cnt);
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log_x(target))
space complexity: O(log_x(target))
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Greedy divide-and-conquer recursion that at each step chooses between using the largest power of x below target or the smallest power above, then recurses on the remainder. Memoization is omitted for brevity but can be added trivially.

